\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces End-to-end accuracy on 134 stratified examples from CLUTRR\_v1 (36 ex), RuleTaker (50 ex), and ProofWriter (48 ex). Overall: RFDE 51.5\%, CoT 57.5\%, LINC 48.5\%, RAG 39.6\%. McNemar test RFDE vs LINC: $p=0.50$ (not significant). RFDE excels on RuleTaker (72\%) but struggles on CLUTRR (11.1\%), suggesting task-specific advantages. Per-dataset breakdown shows high variance by dataset and method, indicating that architectural differences do not uniformly predict outcomes.}}{6}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:accuracy}{{2}{6}{End-to-end accuracy on 134 stratified examples from CLUTRR\_v1 (36 ex), RuleTaker (50 ex), and ProofWriter (48 ex). Overall: RFDE 51.5\%, CoT 57.5\%, LINC 48.5\%, RAG 39.6\%. McNemar test RFDE vs LINC: $p=0.50$ (not significant). RFDE excels on RuleTaker (72\%) but struggles on CLUTRR (11.1\%), suggesting task-specific advantages. Per-dataset breakdown shows high variance by dataset and method, indicating that architectural differences do not uniformly predict outcomes}{figure.2}{}}
